==In Popular Culture==
The fictitious Dr. Martin Ellingham, the main character of British Television's [[Doc Martin]], is a brilliant and successful vascular surgeon at Imperial College London who develops haemophobia (a fear of blood), and as a result is forced to stop practising surgery.

